  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The valley of the son of Hinnom - This valley begins on the west of Jerusalem at the road to Joppa, and turning southeastward round the foot of Mount Zion joins the deeper valley of Kedron on the south of the city. It was in this ravine, more particularly at Tophet in the more wild and precipitous part of it toward the east, that the later kings of Judah offered the sacrifices of children to Moloch (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 33:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). After these places had been defiled by Josiah, Tophet and the whole valley of Hinnom were held in abomination by the Jews, and the name of the latter was used to denote the place of eternal torment ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 5:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Greek term Gehenna (γεέννα  geenna) is in fact formed from the Hebrew הנם גיא  gay' hı̂nnôm, \"valley of Hinnom.\" Hinnom is regarded either as the name of some ancient hero, or as an appellative ( \"groaning\" or \"moaning\"), bestowed on the spot because of the cries of the victims here offered to Moloch, and of the drums with which those cries were drowned.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The valley of the giants - Rather \"the plain of Rephaim.\" This plain, named after an ancient and gigantic tribe of the land Genesis 14:5, lies southwestward of Jerusalem, and is terminated by a slight rocky ridge forming the brow of the valley of Hinnom. The valley is fertile Isaiah 17:5 and broad, and has been on more than one occasion the camping ground for armies operating against Jerusalem 2 Samuel 5:18, 2 Samuel 5:22; 2 Samuel 23:13. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The valley of the giants - Rather \"the plain of Rephaim.\" This plain, named after an ancient and gigantic tribe of the land ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 14:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", lies southwestward of Jerusalem, and is terminated by a slight rocky ridge forming the brow of the valley of Hinnom. The valley is fertile ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 17:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and broad, and has been on more than one occasion the camping ground for armies operating against Jerusalem ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 5:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 5:22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 23:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7. Achor—(see on [194]Jos 7:26).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Adummim—a rising ground in the wilderness of Jericho, on the south of the little brook that flowed near Jericho (Jos 16:1).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "En-shemesh—\"the fountain of the sun\"; \"either the present well of the apostle, below Bethany, on the road to Jericho, or the fountain near to St. Saba\" [Robinson].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "En-rogel—\"the fuller's fountain,\" on the southeast of Jerusalem, below the spot where the valleys of Jehoshaphat and Hinnom unite.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The border went up; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " properly, for the line went from Jordan and the Salt Sea, to the higher grounds nigh Jerusalem; and therefore the line is said to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "go down",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Joshua 18:16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 18:16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", because there it takes a contrary course, and goes downwards to Jordan and the sea. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Hinnom; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a very pleasant place, but afterwards made infamous, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 2 Kings 23:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 23:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Of the Jebusite, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of the city of the Jebusites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which was anciently called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jebusi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Joshua 18:28 Judges 19:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 18:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 19:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The same is Jerusalem:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it may seem hence, and from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Deu 33:12 Joshua 18:28 Judges 1:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deu 33:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 18:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 1:21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that Jerusalem, properly, or at least principally, belonged to Benjamin; and yet it is ascribed to Judah also here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Joshua 15:63",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 15:63",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and elsewhere, either because a part of the city was allotted to Judah; or because the Benjamites needed or desired the help and conjunction of this powerful tribe of Judah, for the getting and keeping of this most important place. And when the Benjamites had in vain attempted to drive out the Jebusites, this work was at last done by the tribe of Judah, who therefore had an interest in it by the right of war; as Ziklag, which belonged to the tribe of Simeon, being gotten from the Philistines by David, was adjoined by him to his tribe of Judah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 1 Samuel 27:6",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Samuel 27:6",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
